        <updateDate>2021-09-13T14:34:44Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Metropolitan Statistical Area Preservation Act</strong></p> <p>This bill prohibits the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) from establishing, for purposes of designating areas as metropolitan statistical areas (MSAs), a minimum population for the urban area of such MSA that is more than 50,000. </p> <p>The OMB may, for statistical purposes only, establish other statistical area designations with higher minimum population requirements for such urban areas.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
